               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a1.-a2.&lt;/b&gt; The metrical part follows a meter of 4x12 syllables with a rhythm of 5/7.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a1.&lt;/b&gt; The form &lt;i&gt;uppālṣi&lt;/i&gt; is nom. pl. m. of the adjective &lt;i&gt;uppālṣe&lt;/i&gt;, which is metri causa for the expected nom. pl. f. &lt;i&gt;uppālṣana&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b1.&lt;/b&gt; The form &lt;i&gt;alyaiṅk&lt;/i&gt; stands for the nom. pl. m. &lt;i&gt;alyaik&lt;/i&gt; which is found in all other instances. It is analogical from the obl. pl. m. which apparently shows a stem with nasal, cf. &lt;i&gt;alyeṅkäṃ&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;     
